Where we act as an Agent of a HIC under PHIPA s. 17, the HIC is the
accountable party and we operate under their authority.

## 2. Personal health information (PHI) — what it is

PHI means identifying information about an individual relating to
their physical or mental health (including health-history information
of family members), the provision of health care, payment or
eligibility for health care, donation of body parts or substances,
health-number identifiers, and substitute-decision-maker information,
as defined in PHIPA s. 4(1).

