## 9. Your rights under PHIPA

- **Access** to your record (PHIPA s. 52): 30-day default response,
  extendable to 60 days in specific circumstances. Some exceptions
  apply.
- **Correction** of inaccurate or incomplete PHI (PHIPA s. 55).
- **Withdrawal of consent** (subject to statutory exceptions).
- **Complaint** — first to us at `[fill in: privacy contact]`, then
  to the IPC at <https://www.ipc.on.ca/en/health-organizations> or
  the IPC's complaints page.

## 10. Safeguards

We use administrative, technical, and physical safeguards proportional
to the sensitivity of PHI (PHIPA s. 12). Highlights:

- Encryption in transit and at rest.
- Role-based and least-privilege access.
- Audit logging of all PHI access (PHIPA s. 10.1) — see
  [`audit-log-requirements.md`](audit-log-requirements.md).
- Secure account-recovery flows that do not bypass the safeguards
  above.
- Vendor due diligence (see [`subprocessors.md`](subprocessors.md)).
- Breach response runbook (see [`breach-response.md`](breach-response.md))
  rehearsed periodically.

## 11. Breach notification

If we determine that your PHI has been stolen, lost, or used or
disclosed without authority, we will notify you at the first
reasonable opportunity in writing (PHIPA s. 12.2). The notice will
inform you of your right to complain to the IPC.

## 12. Retention

PHI retention is governed by the applicable College's records-retention
guidelines (often 10+ years from last contact, longer for minors) and
by any contractual or statutory obligation. `[fill in: specific
